reviews_data.review_text:
Pricy, big space,
Good decor, good location , food was fine not amazing
We ordered two lattes, ham and cheese on a baguette and a biscuit breakfast
Great service.  The Macarons are good but I’ve certainly had better.   Curious if they actually make them in house.
Got it all!!

The atmosphere is the best. The team is kind and very helpful. The food is fantastic. So good in fact I brought some home for my family. One flight, two airports, uber, and a drive home and this team did such a good job packaging the goods it looks like I just left the bakery. I highly recommend this this bakery!!

Loved the vibe!
The food was great, the pastries really good, the coffee could improve a bit, but still good. The prices are good too.
Awesome customer service and Amazing pastries!
AMAZING!  SOOOOOO GOOD and the staff is amazing. I had a hard time ordering because I couldn't decide. They were so patient and helpful!

Great prices for the two items I got! Staff was very friendly and the wait time was low, which made the experience even better. The inside atmosphere is cozy and welcoming—perfect spot to stop by any time of day, and I love that they open early. Convenient location too.

I ordered the almond croissant with a coffee (about $10 total). The coffee had a nice flavor - not bland at all. The almond croissant was a good size with a sweet breading that’s a little different from others I’ve tried - would prefer regular croissant breading. Overall, I’d come back if I was in the area again 😊
This is supposed to be a latte. What a disappointment. No foam. No design. Is there even any coffee in this? We've been coming to Amelie's for years and have never been disappointed until today.

We loved this French Bakery while we visited Charlotte.  It's is a casual service style restaurant where you order your treats at a counter and then pick up your order at a window, but it has all the comforts of a dine in restaurants; there is no table service. It has a beautiful interior with wonderful artworks and designs all over the restaurant.  It gave it such a relaxing atmosphere.  We only went for the delicious pastry and tried the quiche. They did not disappoint and the prices were so reasonable. Highly recommend it if you are in Charlotte for a stop as it is convenient to the Charlotte Convention Center and the Uptown area. They serve French style breakfast and sandwiches as well. Maybe when we are back in town we will be able to try the other items on the menu.
We came to this place since it has good review for its sweets. I really like the fruit tart, it’s soooo good! and being one place in town you should visit if you’re craving for sweets.

Very cute French bakery/café downtown Charlotte.

Staff were extremely helpful and patient, as well as very efficient.

We ordered to go and all of the sweets survived the 2 hr drive home.

We ordered 2 of their 4" tarts: one Raspberry Lemon and one Chocolate Peanut Butter.

The tarts were the best thing we ordered by far! We will definitely stop by to get more of those if we are ever in the area!

We also ordered an eclaír. It was standard. Delicious, but nothing spectacular.

They have a very large selection of macaron flavors - from classic to adventurous.

We ordered 6 macarons of various flavors: (left to right) Lavender Lemon, Raspberry, Cookie Dough, Pistachio, Coffee, and Honey. Every flavor we tried was great. Their macaron selection is definitely a huge pull for business.

We did not try any of their coffee or food, as we only stopped in for dessert. But they have something for everyone. It's worth it to stop in and see what they have in store!

reviews_data.review_text: I believe this place got worse over the years, the bakery doesn't produce anything extraordinary anymore.Its a bit sad to see it but that's my own personal experience.Try it for yourself

Very nice place to get pastry or sanwich or coffe .
Enough rooom to seat and walk inside .the food is great .
The decoration pretty good.
Perfect service, food, atmosphere, and price! Glad we got to stop by
The best pastry I ever had. Cool place for date. Friends get together or just quick stop for great coffee & treat
Salted caramel brownies are to die for!!!!!!
Always delicious!

So the lemon bar is one of the least delicious lemon bars I have had ever. Too much dough and the dough to dough and not crisp on the lemon bar.  The pecan pie tart delicious crisp crust nice salt to balance the sweet of the pecan pie filling solid and classic.  The Napoleon was also super good,nice cream that was not too sweet, could yse like vanilla bean or something to make it more nuanced, even so, lovely pastry layers and worth eating.  But the macaron were really hit or miss.  The blueberry cheesecake was pretty flavorless, the honey good and tasted of honey and the cookie dough on point.  All in all this place has a great selection with prompt service and a blend of lovely and nothing special items.  The interior is kind of costume-ish but charming.  Worth going...for the fun of the experience but go in knowi g the food is inconsistent.

They have GF items but they do not label anything gf because there is not dedicated baking/refrigerated space and thst makes everything subject to cross contamination.  This is a shame...a bit more effort and they could serve an under served demographic.

We really enjoyed our visit here! Needed a quick bite to eat and coffee, this was in walking distance from our hotel. Staff were so kind and patient with us, helping us understand their products and substitutions that could be made. I hope to go back one day!
Great coffee and baked items.   Service was poor - multiple errors in serving two cups of coffee.
Love this café! The coffee was really good as were the croissants and muffins. We visited twice over our stay in Charlotte. Highly recommended.
The best. Did you get that .it's the best.
Staff were extremely nice and the food is amazing!
What a cute place with great choices for a sweet treat and coffee or lunch
Great food ambiance and lots to look at. I recomend the pecan pastry delicious

So my total was $9.53 , I gave her $10 and told her to keep the change . She told me she Don’t take any cash unless if it’s exact change. What kind of customer service is this ? What’s the problem if she took the $10 .I didn’t ask for change either. Her attitude wouldn’t even make me pay with my card: if you don’t like your job get something else.

Amelie’s Bakery is an absolute gem! The moment you walk in, you’re greeted by the most beautiful, whimsical decor that feels like stepping into a Parisian dream. Every detail is thoughtfully designed, creating a cozy yet artistic atmosphere that’s perfect for relaxing or catching up with friends.

And the food? Absolutely incredible. From the flaky croissants to the decadent pastries and savory bites, everything is fresh, flavorful, and crafted with love. You can truly taste the quality in every bite.

Whether you’re grabbing a coffee or indulging in a full spread of treats, Amelie’s delivers a magical experience every time. Highly recommend!

I look for local cafés on every trip I go on. This has been my favorite. I came here every day of my trip after I discovered it! Almond croissant was fresh and delicious every time! Caramel cappuccino was my perfect pick me up daily ❤️

The sweet employee recommended the chocolate Pettit geteaux…it was the most amazing thing ever and definitely not petite
You have to try this!
It was quiet on a Saturday afternoon
Delicious baked croissants, cinnamon rolls and more!

Well, I think I’d be willing to come back here to give it another try with such high reviews, but the food honestly wasn’t that great. Maybe I came on a bad day. I love French bakeries but  I was just disappointed. The Americano I got was super weak. I went to an Italian bakery right after I visited here, and the americano coffee was just night and day. The quiche was completely out of balance and not mixed well. I was getting whole bites that were nothing but bacon crumbles with no egg which made it extremely salty and chewy. I ended up just busting the whole thing up and mixing it better. I love meat in a meat quiche, but that bacon was just completely overpowering. Also, the cheese on top was like leather. I could not cut through it with my fork and I had to wrestle with it to get through. It was like it had it had been reheated multiple times or it’s just the wrong cheese to be putting on top of a quiche. French bakeries do not use as much sugar as American bakeries, but both my orange cream puff and my blueberry tartlet were over the top sweet. American baking style sweet not French. This place was within walking distance of my hotel, so I think next time I will just get a pain chocolat if I get a chance to come back when I’m in town.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Very basic American with a slight flare of French influence. Let's be honest, every Frenchman that will walk this establishment will run away. Completely edible but you better find a different spot if you want a good breakfast.

Great little bakery. Although I wouldn’t constitute them as a true French bakery, they do a decent job, food was pretty good but you can tell it’s not authentic enough. The space is huge but tables and dining area aren’t always the cleanest.
Great environment all around. Excellent food. A number one spot to visit in my book!!!
if you like homemade macaroons, tarts, pastries, brownies and mousse then you will enjoy this place. Nice ambience and place to sit and enjoy.
Excellent coffee shop

Truly the best place to have business outings, fancy lunch, or a place to get work done! Amazing food, service, but you might want to bring a jacket! And the best part? All the food is so fairly priced. All food is around $10, pastries and coffees around $6. You can be in and out feeling full for no more than $20, which is really impressive for how clean and professional their staff is. Best and most affordable and quality food in all of uptown.
Love it
Chocolate ganache macaroons were amazing....melt in my mouth delicious!

The aesthetic of this place is so cute. Had an iced Americano and it was delicious and strong (the way I like it).  Bought a variety of desserts.. but my favorite was the coconut macaron. SOOOO GOOD, tried to just take a bite of everything but ended up eating that entire thing.

I enjoyed reading a book over cappuccino and a couple delicious macaroons, while waiting on my appointment. The design is fun and playful- mix and match of different chairs, tables, chandeliers in such large space is unique to Amelie's. Great location. Quiet enough to relax.

My friends and I were trying to find a cute little spot for a light brunch and Amélie’s was perfect! I have a gluten sensitivity so checked the menu ahead of time. They were out of the GF almond pastry when I got there, so I got a crème brûlée and a strawberry cheesecake macaron instead. Both items were so delicious. The staff was so kind about letting me know what all was GF. The macaron was so good I got more to go; red velvet, chocolate, strawberry cheesecake, cotton candy, and the blueberry one. They were all amazing, but my overall favorite was the red velvet. I definitely recommend trying this bakery. The only thing I got and didn’t like was the strawberry white chocolate latte. It was way too sweet at the bottom and not sweet enough at the top, and was impossible to mix. So just keep that in mind when ordering coffee. My friends got their raspberry tea and some sparkling strawberry drink (not sure of the name) and they loved them. They also do free refills of the tea which is always a plus! The atmosphere is also wonderful. The decor is precious and unlike anything you’d see elsewhere. I loved Amélie’s and will be back :)

I forgot to take pictures, but we stopped by for a takeout coffee and pastry for breakfast one weekday. It looked like they had some interesting themed seating for dine in customers. The menu was extensive, so there were a ton of coffee and pastry choices. As a visitor, I love going to places like this that just make the coffee experience so much more enjoyable. I would love to return and try something else next time I'm in town!
Enjoyed the pastries and lattes!

reviews_data.review_text: I don't get the hype. I've been several times and have tried different pastries and drinks. Most of the time the pastries are dried out. They lack flavor. They're overpriced for what they are. My last straw is the coffee I ordered and received with spoiled, curdled half and half in it. How can you serve something with obvious chunks in it? Disgusting.
Thank you so much, very delicious!
These were our best choices yet. We always try something new. As usual the service was welcoming and warm. One of our favorite dessert places.

reviews_data.review_text: This was my go to bakery in college from 09-12. The croissants are the closest to France you’ll get 🥐 can’t wait to visit and get a breakfast sandwich. Sausage egg and cheese on a fresh croissant. Yum 😋
I came here with my family for breakfast. Delicious food, friendly staff and great relaxed atmosphere
Best place for a treat or a bite of pure deliciousness.
Love the decor
The pasties are overly sweet to my taste. Nice coffee and friendly staff though. Cool atmosphere and decor. Would recommend if you happen to be around.
Really good food, great coffee.
Ok food for a french bakery.
Good desserts
What an oddly little charming coffee shop. Coffee was good and food was decent.

Went on a Sunday during lunch expecting it to be busy. Service time was fine but sounds in the room made it hard to hear and speak.

The restaurant  was out of items and you don't find that out until you wait in line to order. A sign would be nice.

Because they were out an ingredient for a sandwich, instead of just subbing out the missing ingredient, they up-charged me for a "create your own". I didn't create this, y'all did it for me. It's only $2 but I shouldn't be charged for the restaurants missing inventory.

Speaking and debating with the cashier didn't seem appropriate for how many other people were waiting behind possibly to be disappointed as well.

Food was good, a little rich for my taste. A little sloppily put together.

reviews_data.review_text: I really had my hopes up after reading reviews of Amelie's but it just wasn't good. I ordered a large tiramisu latte after reading reviews and my cup was only half full when I went to take my first sip! When I went to say something to the barista, she added steamed milk to the top of it. It pretty much ruined it. I didn't complain because it just seemed like the people who worked there didn't care. From the person who took our order, to the barista, to the person who called out our name at the food window. Our sandwiches were sad and lacking, nothing special. What keeps it at 3 stars, instead of 1, were the treats from the baked goods! I tried macarons for the first time and they were delicious. I just feel like for the cool atmosphere of this place and for what we spent, it should have, and could have, been a lot better. I will definitely try another place when I am in Charlotte next time.

Had a raspberry macaroon and caramel brownie. The macaroon was good but the brownie was too sweet for me. There is a mixture of seating, some of it wheelchair accessible. Some people working on their laptops, but the background music and noise from other patrons is pretty loud.

Some of the pastries we ordered were very good, like the pecan and blueberry tarts. I didn't give 5 stars bc I tasted some that were dry and not flavorful. I loved the art indoors but didn't love the seating. Worth a visit to get a quick sugar fix.
Love this place!! Atmosphere is FABULOUS, food is DIVINE, and I adored all the Paris decorations. I would be here all the time if I lived here. My new fav place away from home.
Love this place - great food & great people!!
Definitely recommend the Raspberry Agave Lemonade! Staff were nice and helpful. Plenty of tables and seating (inside and outside). Love this place!

reviews_data.review_text: Really cool and well designed location. The French Dip sandwich was banging!! As was the cappuccino.
The food is amazing, the atmosphere is delightful and the staff is super nice.

So glad we stopped by during a short trip to Charlotte! What a gorgeous bakery with stunning desserts! The staff was so helpful and friendly, describing all the pastries we asked about. I ordered the Oreo Entremet and they slipped in a mini peanut butter tart! Both were absolutely delicious! They were not overly sweet and all the components were so complementary of each other. My friend got macarons to take home to her family. It’s a bonus to find out their macarons were featured in the Hunger Games! Definitely a must stop by if you’re in town!
Tranquilo, cómodo y espacioso. Preciosa decoración y sabrosa comida
What a phenomenal place! The pastries are delicious! The coffee was great! I’ll be back to eat something savory off the menu next time!

Fun decor in this cute cafe is what we came for! The food was decent as well. We didn’t get to try the pastries, especially the macaroons - saving it for another time!

Surely give this place a visit for those Instagram-worthy clicks 📸

reviews_data.review_text: So good!

Amélie’s is a gem in downtown Charlotte. The atmosphere is cozy and artsy, perfect for catching up with a friend or just relaxing with a good pastry. Everything we tried was delicious — fresh, flavorful, and clearly made with care. The staff was friendly and patient while we took our time deciding (so many tempting options!). Can’t wait to come back and try more.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is quirky, fun, and delicious. Not to mention, despite having a steady flow of customers and a decently long line, service was prompt and every one was so polite and helpful! We each got an entree and a pastry/sweet. Between the four of us, we tried the breakfast wrap, two different build-your-own sandwiches, a croque monsieur, chocolate croissant, cheese danish, chocolate chip cookie, fruit tart, two lattes and a tea! Every thing was fresh and yummy. The fruit tart was a favorite. The tiramasu latte was amazing; one of the best lattes I've ever had! Each main item (sandwiches & wraps) are around $9-10 and the pastries ran $4-7, I think. So if you want to try many things, it can get a bit pricey. But the quality is great, service is quick, and the vibe is fun!

The quiche with meat was so salty my husband could not eat it. My egg and potato bowl was cold so they remade it and I specifically asked for it hot and it was cold again. Yelling out people’s name to pick up their orders. Not my kind of place. Coffee was good.
Great pastries and excelente custumer service
Always visit Amelie's when we come home.
Terrible, cold food , frozen pastry not fresh , no toliet paper, no paper towels . Down town one .

When your political beliefs become your identity - you know you're at Amelie's. The coffee isn't worth the price, the pastries aren't great, and the environment is cookie-cutter. Nothing special or unique here.

review_questions.Parking options: Paid street parking

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was great as well as espresso. Their pastry selection was fresh and very delicious! My partner had the quice and it was fresh, warm, and had an amazing crispy crust!!!

Found it odd that at 7:30am on a Thursday morning, they were already out of food items (breakfast wrap and sausage). The food that I was able to order was good - purchased the biscuit buttermilk sandwich. I would've ordered coffee but I was unimpressed with their coffee/espresso machine.
The dining are gives me Alice in Wonderland/Mad Hatter vibes.  It's super cool and the food is delicious.

We enjoyed the food and loved the eclairs but the service was disorganized and unhelpful. After picking up our food, we had to return to "the red window" to request spoons and wait for some to be washed,  then to ask for salt and pepper (which for some reason came in tiny plastic cups), and then again for a to-go container after the bus boy said he could not get one for us. We started to feel like servers rather than customers.
What a wonderful place to get coffee and pastries

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome pastries
We got tarts and a chocolate mousse with our coffee and tea order. There was nothing French about the pastries except maybe the price. Coffee was fine. Counter help was friendly.

Glad I don't live in Charlotte or I would be there 2x a week.
Excellent all around

Amélie's Uptown is such a unique find! Walking in, it felt a bit like stepping into an Alice in Wonderland-inspired world—without Alice. Whimsical, artistic, and full of charm. The decor is incredibly creative and unlike anything I've seen before. The food was delicious ! A truly unique experience—highly recommend if you're looking for something different and delightful!

We dined in, which, of course, you have to do. We ordered the Chicken + Pesto + Goat Cheese Sandwich and the Croque Monsieur for our entree. For dessert, we ordered the Napolean and the Chocolate Petit Gateaux. All of it was amazing, but I definitely enjoyed the chicken and Napolean the most.
The food was excellent and the atmosphere was super cute! The prices were very reasonable considering the location in the heart of downtown Charlotte. I can't wait to go again.

We ordered the creme brulee and it tasted like straight egg. Like it might as well as be scrambled eggs, and we werent able to finish eating it as it was kinda disgusting and ive never tasted a creme brulee that bad. I brought it to their attention and they said they can't give a refund but I could replace it. I thought I might pay a price difference or at least get my replacement for free, but instead they tried to charge me full price. Highly unprofessional and inappropriate

Even a basic cappuccino has that deep, rich aroma and smooth taste — really good coffee. Some cool art and chandeliers catch your eye — definitely worth a quick stop. A perfect place to snap some city photos!
What a quaint "little " bakery/bistro right in downtown Charlotte! Specialty coffee and the Cinnamon roll was amazing and the lunch items smelled delicious as well!

From out of town, visiting for a festival. This café was recommended by several locals for breakfast. Nice atmosphere and delicious pastries. The lemon raspberry was yummy. Unfortunately there was a mix up picking up my order from the dine in window, and while every employee aware was working to resolve the mix up, an employee named Zach was extremely rude and condescending about me and my responsibility to get my order in ear shot of me and many other customers waiting beside me. Because another employee was so helpful, I did not say anything about his rudenss and thanked her. I understand things happened and would very rarely directly call out an employee but this level of rudeness is worthy of it and I can only assume Zach is an owner or related to an owner for this behavior to be tolerated. I would return, but I would request Zach not be involved in my service.
Amazing 👏
Fantastic!
My favorite iced coffee in Charlotte so far. The cream cheese pastry was great as well.
Fun experience!
Food and service were terrible. Don't be distracted by the crazy decor. Atmosphere and decor were both way too loud

Amélie’s French Bakery & Café in Uptown Charlotte is a whimsical retreat that delights both the palate and the senses. The café’s eclectic décor features mismatched chandeliers, including one crafted entirely from silverware, adding to its quirky charm. Guests can indulge in signature pastries like the famed Salted Caramel Brownie, alongside a variety of French-inspired treats and beverages. Whether you’re seeking a cozy spot for coffee or a unique backdrop for conversation, Amélie’s offers a memorable experience in the heart of the city.

reviews_data.review_text: Fun place, good food, helpful staff
Cute French Cafe in Charlotte

I walked in with high expectations, drawn by the French name of the pastry shop, hoping for delicate desserts with the balanced flavors typical of French patisserie. Unfortunately, the reality was quite different. The pastries were overwhelmingly sweet and heavy, more reminiscent of American-style desserts than anything French. Disappointing overall.
Very long line, but only because food and ambiance was totally worth it!

I stopped by to grab some pastries and decided to stay and have a bite for lunch. I was assisted by two different employees, one who was very sweet and helpful, one who was dismissive, rushed (they weren’t very busy), and kind of rude.
I ordered a “tartine” with fig jam, Brie, and bacon. The baguette was sub par and borderline stale, the Brie was obviously a crème style product, and the bacon was low quality. Every time I tried to take a bite, the full slices of bacon would pull off the entire piece of bread. Just a poorly constructed afterthought.
The “salad” consisted of two GIANT pieces of kale, a few smaller torn pieces, and toppings that I ended up basically eating by themselves. I mean, completely inedible as salad. I could have gotten up and asked for a knife, but I already felt as though I was fighting for my life just trying to consume this meal peacefully, so I gave up. I actually don’t think I would go back.
The three stars are for the pastries which were decent, the one nice employee, and the ambiance.

Super cool little bistro with a hip vibe. A couple was here dressed to the nines and taking pictures in the awesome decor (though it would have been nice if they weren't in the way of people actually buying and eating things). Great food, the desserts on point, and the tartlets do travel well crosscountry!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Pastries, Salted Caramel Brownie, Apple Tart

reviews_data.review_text: A nice pastry shop and cafe with sidewalk seating to enjoy your beverage and relax watching the world like a true Parisian café and pâtisserie
Great selection of bakery. Veggie quiche a tad oily otherwise tasty. Love the decor and motif.

The only French about this place was the music in the restroom. The rest is American -  greasy food, pastries are super sweat, depressing atmosphere inside. Tried to find good coffee place in Charlotte based on reviews and this one was a mistake
amazing coffee and pastries. the cafe is almost a tourist attraction in its self ! It’s an extremely unique place !

Really disappointed. Have come here for a year and order the same thing every. Sadly, something has changed with the torts. Parts of the shell are soggy. The strawberries are water logged and also soggy. This was within a few minutes of ordering. You can see the ring in the box from the wet ring under the tort.
Great breakfast location in downtown Charlotte. A lot of seating inside and out. Great service and great food. Is within walking distance of a lot of hotels in the area. Great experience.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Pastries, Half Dozen Assorted Macarons, Quiche Du Jour, Café Marcotter

reviews_data.review_text: The macarons were great when I went, and the building is so pretty inside. I recommend it to anyone that I know is visiting Charlotte :)
Very nice staff. Delicious pastries.  Ambiance was calming. Strawberry danish and raspberry lemon tart was amazing.

The BEST macarons I have ever had! I stumbled upon this place while I was visiting for the ACC games and I was instantly hooked! Once I found out they shipped macarons, I ordered a dozen to ship. While there was an issue with my order, the manager I spoke to was absolutely phenomenal in getting things back in line and they were there the next day on my door step. If you want a delicious treat..try this place!
Wonderful little bakery in uptown Charlotte! Visit them, you won't be disappointed! I had their twice baked almond croissant- super yummy!

I recently visited on Sunday a French bakery nestled in the vibrant heart of downtown, and it was a delightful experience from start to finish. The ambience immediately stood out—unique and fancy, with an elegant charm that made it feel like a little slice of France amid the urban bustle. The decor was sophisticated yet welcoming, striking a perfect balance that elevated the entire visit.

The location couldn’t be better; being right in the center of downtown made it a convenient stop amidst a busy day, yet it felt like a serene escape from the surrounding hustle. What truly impressed me, though, was the wide range of options to choose from. Whether you’re craving a flaky croissant, a rich éclair, or a perfectly crafted macaron, this bakery has something for every palate. The variety was almost overwhelming—in the best way possible—showcasing authentic French flavors with a modern twist.
Very eclectic bakery and eatery. Very well furnished and dressed. The treats were delicious. Baguette and macarons.

We were hoping to dine at Amelie’s French Bakery & Cafe in uptown today and once again, they were out of quiche. You would think they would know the demand they have from their customers so they would make enough to last through the brunch hour on the weekends. However, they don’t because this happens all the time. In addition, they were out of chicken salad and also turkey so no Monte Cristo. I asked her what did they have and she basically said not a lot except for the bakery items. She said she wish she had a digital menu board so they could wipe out the items that they didn’t have so people would know. That’s not a bad idea however, how about trying to be in stock so you can serve your clientele. It’s a great place to eat when they have the food. Bummer that we had to leave. Maybe next time.

Waited close to an hour to get an unbaked pre-bake baguette like the plastic wrapped ones you buy at a grocery store and a Napoleon with completely frozen cream. Also sold out of croissants, but I think we lucked out not buying more things.
Amazing food. Friendly staff and great atmosphere.
the cashier was very overwhelming and got our orders completely messed up. i much prefer the other locations.

Amélie's is a short walk from the Kimpton hotel.  It sounded tasty, so I randomly decided to check it out one Saturday afternoon. There were plenty of patrons inside but there was no wait. And still plenty of pastries and treats to choose from.

I tried an oat chai latte, and it was delicious. So good in fact that I walked back over the next morning before we had to hit the road. I also got an almond torte, and it was really sweet. More like a dessert than a breakfast pastry.

The cafe itself had the coolest decor. There were several unique chandeliers made of things like pots and pans and kitchen utensils. There's also a lot of fun artwork. The place is huge too, with what appeared to be multiple levels of seating and plenty of tables.

I'd definitely stop by if I'm in town again. They have a whole menu I need to check out.

The food and vibe of this place are great. However, the service was disappointing. The guy with the ponytail at the checkout counter was passive-aggressive for some reason and wasn’t friendly at all. At the end of checkout, it prompts you to join the loyalty program, and I was eager to sign up. However, as I started entering my details, he canceled the screen. Additionally, when I asked him to make my order 'for here,' he ignored my request and made it 'to-go' instead. These small issues really spoiled the mood, and it made it hard to fully enjoy the vibe of the place.

I had the absolute pleasure of enjoying a delicious pastry at Amelie’s, and it was nothing short of delightful. The pastry was perfectly baked—flaky, rich, and bursting with flavor in every bite. You can really taste the love and care that goes into their creations.

Beyond the food, the atmosphere at Amelie’s is fun, vibrant, and full of charm. The eclectic decor and open, welcoming vibe make it the kind of place where you want to linger. Whether you’re catching up with a friend or just enjoying some solo time, it’s a space that instantly lifts your mood.

The staff truly sealed the experience for me. Everyone I interacted with was incredibly friendly, warm, and attentive. They made me feel genuinely welcome and taken care of from the moment I walked in. Amelie’s isn’t just a café—it’s an experience, and I can’t wait to go back.
Love this place

A relaxed french cafe with a great selection of cakes and pastries and good coffee. Especially good when you need to work and be productive in a chill ambience. I ordered fruit tarts and almond cake both were excellent!
Picked up coffees and breakfast for a group of 6 on a Saturday morning, everything came out so fast and was so good.

reviews_data.review_text: I love the aesthetic of this restaurant, it’s very beautiful. In terms of the food though, it was nothing amazing. The restaurant, at its original location (unfortunately lost to rezoning) as well as the one off park road and the one on P-M road, are known for the drinks and food offerings -especially pastries, as well as the friendly staff.

Yet, the big difference (and both my wife and felt the same) is that the uptown locale, because of its size, very high ceilings and lots of open spaces, as well as a very monochrome color scheme, did not give us the same "cozy bistro feeling" that the other ones give. It felt "cold" for lack of a better word.
In this respect, we found it lacking. In every other aspect, it was the same good Amelie's fare and service we have come to know and enjoy.

if you look in the photos, I posted a picture of the mess they gave me. A huge disappointment.

Interesting place that brings a bit of French culture but in an American style. Super tasty sweets, we ordered 4 items and none of them disappointed. I especially loved the Apple cobbler mini tart and the chocolate petit gateau.
I loved the decor and the museum feel it has with different models of chandeliers on the ceiling, mirrors on some walls and paintings. Very different and pleasant. I think it's a perfect stop for a coffee and a sweet between visits to the museum or after an event nearby.

Great vibes, amazing decor, and delicious sweets. A fantastic hangout spot in the middle of downtown to work, relax or catch up with a friend. I only got the napoleon but I'll definitely be back to try their other offerings!

This is a long one…
First obvious context. When I review I consider 3 elements of my experience: atmosphere, service and food. Less obvious, I have worked across the street from Amelie’s for more than 10 yrs, and I LOVE French foods, and honestly, I’m not that hard to please. You’ll have to trust me on this because after reading this review you will doubt me.

Sadly, Amelie’s consistently disappoints me. My biggest gripe is with their ordering, food collection process - it’s confusing and customers end up asking each other questions (“where are the napkins?” You’ll find them across the wide open space far from the cutlery) because the staff seems oblivious to the general confusion and doesn’t set or manage expectations. A few years ago they did a process and space  remodel, but alas, it’s still confusing.

Nonetheless, the food used to lure me in despite this frustration with process and staff’s oblivion. But even that has become ‘meh’- not the pasties mind you they are amazing—  Sometimes heated halfway through, sometimes flavors fall short.

Fortunately for me and my French-food-obsession there are multiple French restaurants in and around CLT.  One that excels where Amelie’s flops, is Chez Marie Patisserie in South Park. They also have amazing pastries, and win on service, attitude and food as well. Plus it’s a darling little space to sit and enjoy life. I don’t work there, I don’t know anyone who works there, I’m just a fan of their sunny spot.

Great service.  The Macarons are good but I’ve certainly had better.   Curious if they actually make them in house.
Got it all!!

The atmosphere is the best. The team is kind and very helpful. The food is fantastic. So good in fact I brought some home for my family. One flight, two airports, uber, and a drive home and this team did such a good job packaging the goods it looks like I just left the bakery. I highly recommend this this bakery!!

Loved the vibe!
The food was great, the pastries really good, the coffee could improve a bit, but still good. The prices are good too.
Awesome customer service and Amazing pastries!
AMAZING!  SOOOOOO GOOD and the staff is amazing. I had a hard time ordering because I couldn't decide. They were so patient and helpful!

Great prices for the two items I got! Staff was very friendly and the wait time was low, which made the experience even better. The inside atmosphere is cozy and welcoming—perfect spot to stop by any time of day, and I love that they open early. Convenient location too.

I ordered the almond croissant with a coffee (about $10 total). The coffee had a nice flavor - not bland at all. The almond croissant was a good size with a sweet breading that’s a little different from others I’ve tried - would prefer regular croissant breading. Overall, I’d come back if I was in the area again 😊
This is supposed to be a latte. What a disappointment. No foam. No design. Is there even any coffee in this? We've been coming to Amelie's for years and have never been disappointed until today.

We loved this French Bakery while we visited Charlotte.  It's is a casual service style restaurant where you order your treats at a counter and then pick up your order at a window, but it has all the comforts of a dine in restaurants; there is no table service. It has a beautiful interior with wonderful artworks and designs all over the restaurant.  It gave it such a relaxing atmosphere.  We only went for the delicious pastry and tried the quiche. They did not disappoint and the prices were so reasonable. Highly recommend it if you are in Charlotte for a stop as it is convenient to the Charlotte Convention Center and the Uptown area. They serve French style breakfast and sandwiches as well. Maybe when we are back in town we will be able to try the other items on the menu.
We came to this place since it has good review for its sweets. I really like the fruit tart, it’s soooo good! and being one place in town you should visit if you’re craving for sweets.

Very cute French bakery/café downtown Charlotte.

Staff were extremely helpful and patient, as well as very efficient.

We ordered to go and all of the sweets survived the 2 hr drive home.

We ordered 2 of their 4" tarts: one Raspberry Lemon and one Chocolate Peanut Butter.

The tarts were the best thing we ordered by far! We will definitely stop by to get more of those if we are ever in the area!

We also ordered an eclaír. It was standard. Delicious, but nothing spectacular.

They have a very large selection of macaron flavors - from classic to adventurous.

We ordered 6 macarons of various flavors: (left to right) Lavender Lemon, Raspberry, Cookie Dough, Pistachio, Coffee, and Honey. Every flavor we tried was great. Their macaron selection is definitely a huge pull for business.

We did not try any of their coffee or food, as we only stopped in for dessert. But they have something for everyone. It's worth it to stop in and see what they have in store!

Very nice place to get pastry or sanwich or coffe .
Enough rooom to seat and walk inside .the food is great .
The decoration pretty good.
Perfect service, food, atmosphere, and price! Glad we got to stop by
The best pastry I ever had. Cool place for date. Friends get together or just quick stop for great coffee & treat
Salted caramel brownies are to die for!!!!!!
Always delicious!

So the lemon bar is one of the least delicious lemon bars I have had ever. Too much dough and the dough to dough and not crisp on the lemon bar.  The pecan pie tart delicious crisp crust nice salt to balance the sweet of the pecan pie filling solid and classic.  The Napoleon was also super good,nice cream that was not too sweet, could yse like vanilla bean or something to make it more nuanced, even so, lovely pastry layers and worth eating.  But the macaron were really hit or miss.  The blueberry cheesecake was pretty flavorless, the honey good and tasted of honey and the cookie dough on point.  All in all this place has a great selection with prompt service and a blend of lovely and nothing special items.  The interior is kind of costume-ish but charming.  Worth going...for the fun of the experience but go in knowi g the food is inconsistent.

They have GF items but they do not label anything gf because there is not dedicated baking/refrigerated space and thst makes everything subject to cross contamination.  This is a shame...a bit more effort and they could serve an under served demographic.

We really enjoyed our visit here! Needed a quick bite to eat and coffee, this was in walking distance from our hotel. Staff were so kind and patient with us, helping us understand their products and substitutions that could be made. I hope to go back one day!
Great coffee and baked items.   Service was poor - multiple errors in serving two cups of coffee.
Love this café! The coffee was really good as were the croissants and muffins. We visited twice over our stay in Charlotte. Highly recommended.
The best. Did you get that .it's the best.
Staff were extremely nice and the food is amazing!
What a cute place with great choices for a sweet treat and coffee or lunch
Great food ambiance and lots to look at. I recomend the pecan pastry delicious

So my total was $9.53 , I gave her $10 and told her to keep the change . She told me she Don’t take any cash unless if it’s exact change. What kind of customer service is this ? What’s the problem if she took the $10 .I didn’t ask for change either. Her attitude wouldn’t even make me pay with my card: if you don’t like your job get something else.

Amelie’s Bakery is an absolute gem! The moment you walk in, you’re greeted by the most beautiful, whimsical decor that feels like stepping into a Parisian dream. Every detail is thoughtfully designed, creating a cozy yet artistic atmosphere that’s perfect for relaxing or catching up with friends.

And the food? Absolutely incredible. From the flaky croissants to the decadent pastries and savory bites, everything is fresh, flavorful, and crafted with love. You can truly taste the quality in every bite.

Whether you’re grabbing a coffee or indulging in a full spread of treats, Amelie’s delivers a magical experience every time. Highly recommend!

I look for local cafés on every trip I go on. This has been my favorite. I came here every day of my trip after I discovered it! Almond croissant was fresh and delicious every time! Caramel cappuccino was my perfect pick me up daily ❤️

The sweet employee recommended the chocolate Pettit geteaux…it was the most amazing thing ever and definitely not petite
You have to try this!
It was quiet on a Saturday afternoon
Delicious baked croissants, cinnamon rolls and more!

Well, I think I’d be willing to come back here to give it another try with such high reviews, but the food honestly wasn’t that great. Maybe I came on a bad day. I love French bakeries but  I was just disappointed. The Americano I got was super weak. I went to an Italian bakery right after I visited here, and the americano coffee was just night and day. The quiche was completely out of balance and not mixed well. I was getting whole bites that were nothing but bacon crumbles with no egg which made it extremely salty and chewy. I ended up just busting the whole thing up and mixing it better. I love meat in a meat quiche, but that bacon was just completely overpowering. Also, the cheese on top was like leather. I could not cut through it with my fork and I had to wrestle with it to get through. It was like it had it had been reheated multiple times or it’s just the wrong cheese to be putting on top of a quiche. French bakeries do not use as much sugar as American bakeries, but both my orange cream puff and my blueberry tartlet were over the top sweet. American baking style sweet not French. This place was within walking distance of my hotel, so I think next time I will just get a pain chocolat if I get a chance to come back when I’m in town.

reviews_data.review_text: Very basic American with a slight flare of French influence. Let's be honest, every Frenchman that will walk this establishment will run away. Completely edible but you better find a different spot if you want a good breakfast.

Great little bakery. Although I wouldn’t constitute them as a true French bakery, they do a decent job, food was pretty good but you can tell it’s not authentic enough. The space is huge but tables and dining area aren’t always the cleanest.
Great environment all around. Excellent food. A number one spot to visit in my book!!!
if you like homemade macaroons, tarts, pastries, brownies and mousse then you will enjoy this place. Nice ambience and place to sit and enjoy.
Excellent coffee shop

Truly the best place to have business outings, fancy lunch, or a place to get work done! Amazing food, service, but you might want to bring a jacket! And the best part? All the food is so fairly priced. All food is around $10, pastries and coffees around $6. You can be in and out feeling full for no more than $20, which is really impressive for how clean and professional their staff is. Best and most affordable and quality food in all of uptown.
Love it
Chocolate ganache macaroons were amazing....melt in my mouth delicious!

The aesthetic of this place is so cute. Had an iced Americano and it was delicious and strong (the way I like it).  Bought a variety of desserts.. but my favorite was the coconut macaron. SOOOO GOOD, tried to just take a bite of everything but ended up eating that entire thing.

I enjoyed reading a book over cappuccino and a couple delicious macaroons, while waiting on my appointment. The design is fun and playful- mix and match of different chairs, tables, chandeliers in such large space is unique to Amelie's. Great location. Quiet enough to relax.

My friends and I were trying to find a cute little spot for a light brunch and Amélie’s was perfect! I have a gluten sensitivity so checked the menu ahead of time. They were out of the GF almond pastry when I got there, so I got a crème brûlée and a strawberry cheesecake macaron instead. Both items were so delicious. The staff was so kind about letting me know what all was GF. The macaron was so good I got more to go; red velvet, chocolate, strawberry cheesecake, cotton candy, and the blueberry one. They were all amazing, but my overall favorite was the red velvet. I definitely recommend trying this bakery. The only thing I got and didn’t like was the strawberry white chocolate latte. It was way too sweet at the bottom and not sweet enough at the top, and was impossible to mix. So just keep that in mind when ordering coffee. My friends got their raspberry tea and some sparkling strawberry drink (not sure of the name) and they loved them. They also do free refills of the tea which is always a plus! The atmosphere is also wonderful. The decor is precious and unlike anything you’d see elsewhere. I loved Amélie’s and will be back :)

I forgot to take pictures, but we stopped by for a takeout coffee and pastry for breakfast one weekday. It looked like they had some interesting themed seating for dine in customers. The menu was extensive, so there were a ton of coffee and pastry choices. As a visitor, I love going to places like this that just make the coffee experience so much more enjoyable. I would love to return and try something else next time I'm in town!
Enjoyed the pastries and lattes!

I came here with my family for breakfast. Delicious food, friendly staff and great relaxed atmosphere
Best place for a treat or a bite of pure deliciousness.

Really good food, great coffee.
Ok food for a french bakery.
Good desserts
What an oddly little charming coffee shop. Coffee was good and food was decent.

Went on a Sunday during lunch expecting it to be busy. Service time was fine but sounds in the room made it hard to hear and speak.

The restaurant  was out of items and you don't find that out until you wait in line to order. A sign would be nice.

Because they were out an ingredient for a sandwich, instead of just subbing out the missing ingredient, they up-charged me for a "create your own". I didn't create this, y'all did it for me. It's only $2 but I shouldn't be charged for the restaurants missing inventory.

Speaking and debating with the cashier didn't seem appropriate for how many other people were waiting behind possibly to be disappointed as well.

Food was good, a little rich for my taste. A little sloppily put together.

reviews_data.review_text: I really had my hopes up after reading reviews of Amelie's but it just wasn't good. I ordered a large tiramisu latte after reading reviews and my cup was only half full when I went to take my first sip! When I went to say something to the barista, she added steamed milk to the top of it. It pretty much ruined it. I didn't complain because it just seemed like the people who worked there didn't care. From the person who took our order, to the barista, to the person who called out our name at the food window. Our sandwiches were sad and lacking, nothing special. What keeps it at 3 stars, instead of 1, were the treats from the baked goods! I tried macarons for the first time and they were delicious. I just feel like for the cool atmosphere of this place and for what we spent, it should have, and could have, been a lot better. I will definitely try another place when I am in Charlotte next time.

Had a raspberry macaroon and caramel brownie. The macaroon was good but the brownie was too sweet for me. There is a mixture of seating, some of it wheelchair accessible. Some people working on their laptops, but the background music and noise from other patrons is pretty loud.

Some of the pastries we ordered were very good, like the pecan and blueberry tarts. I didn't give 5 stars bc I tasted some that were dry and not flavorful. I loved the art indoors but didn't love the seating. Worth a visit to get a quick sugar fix.
Love this place!! Atmosphere is FABULOUS, food is DIVINE, and I adored all the Paris decorations. I would be here all the time if I lived here. My new fav place away from home.
Love this place - great food & great people!!
Definitely recommend the Raspberry Agave Lemonade! Staff were nice and helpful. Plenty of tables and seating (inside and outside). Love this place!

The food is amazing, the atmosphere is delightful and the staff is super nice.

So glad we stopped by during a short trip to Charlotte! What a gorgeous bakery with stunning desserts! The staff was so helpful and friendly, describing all the pastries we asked about. I ordered the Oreo Entremet and they slipped in a mini peanut butter tart! Both were absolutely delicious! They were not overly sweet and all the components were so complementary of each other. My friend got macarons to take home to her family. It’s a bonus to find out their macarons were featured in the Hunger Games! Definitely a must stop by if you’re in town!
Tranquilo, cómodo y espacioso. Preciosa decoración y sabrosa comida
What a phenomenal place! The pastries are delicious! The coffee was great! I’ll be back to eat something savory off the menu next time!

Fun decor in this cute cafe is what we came for! The food was decent as well. We didn’t get to try the pastries, especially the macaroons - saving it for another time!

Surely give this place a visit for those Instagram-worthy clicks 📸

reviews_data.review_text: This place is quirky, fun, and delicious. Not to mention, despite having a steady flow of customers and a decently long line, service was prompt and every one was so polite and helpful! We each got an entree and a pastry/sweet. Between the four of us, we tried the breakfast wrap, two different build-your-own sandwiches, a croque monsieur, chocolate croissant, cheese danish, chocolate chip cookie, fruit tart, two lattes and a tea! Every thing was fresh and yummy. The fruit tart was a favorite. The tiramasu latte was amazing; one of the best lattes I've ever had! Each main item (sandwiches & wraps) are around $9-10 and the pastries ran $4-7, I think. So if you want to try many things, it can get a bit pricey. But the quality is great, service is quick, and the vibe is fun!

The quiche with meat was so salty my husband could not eat it. My egg and potato bowl was cold so they remade it and I specifically asked for it hot and it was cold again. Yelling out people’s name to pick up their orders. Not my kind of place. Coffee was good.
Great pastries and excelente custumer service
Always visit Amelie's when we come home.
Terrible, cold food , frozen pastry not fresh , no toliet paper, no paper towels . Down town one .

When your political beliefs become your identity - you know you're at Amelie's. The coffee isn't worth the price, the pastries aren't great, and the environment is cookie-cutter. Nothing special or unique here.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was great as well as espresso. Their pastry selection was fresh and very delicious! My partner had the quice and it was fresh, warm, and had an amazing crispy crust!!!

Found it odd that at 7:30am on a Thursday morning, they were already out of food items (breakfast wrap and sausage). The food that I was able to order was good - purchased the biscuit buttermilk sandwich. I would've ordered coffee but I was unimpressed with their coffee/espresso machine.
The dining are gives me Alice in Wonderland/Mad Hatter vibes.  It's super cool and the food is delicious.

We enjoyed the food and loved the eclairs but the service was disorganized and unhelpful. After picking up our food, we had to return to "the red window" to request spoons and wait for some to be washed,  then to ask for salt and pepper (which for some reason came in tiny plastic cups), and then again for a to-go container after the bus boy said he could not get one for us. We started to feel like servers rather than customers.

We got tarts and a chocolate mousse with our coffee and tea order. There was nothing French about the pastries except maybe the price. Coffee was fine. Counter help was friendly.

Glad I don't live in Charlotte or I would be there 2x a week.
Excellent all around

Amélie's Uptown is such a unique find! Walking in, it felt a bit like stepping into an Alice in Wonderland-inspired world—without Alice. Whimsical, artistic, and full of charm. The decor is incredibly creative and unlike anything I've seen before. The food was delicious ! A truly unique experience—highly recommend if you're looking for something different and delightful!

We dined in, which, of course, you have to do. We ordered the Chicken + Pesto + Goat Cheese Sandwich and the Croque Monsieur for our entree. For dessert, we ordered the Napolean and the Chocolate Petit Gateaux. All of it was amazing, but I definitely enjoyed the chicken and Napolean the most.
The food was excellent and the atmosphere was super cute! The prices were very reasonable considering the location in the heart of downtown Charlotte. I can't wait to go again.

We ordered the creme brulee and it tasted like straight egg. Like it might as well as be scrambled eggs, and we werent able to finish eating it as it was kinda disgusting and ive never tasted a creme brulee that bad. I brought it to their attention and they said they can't give a refund but I could replace it. I thought I might pay a price difference or at least get my replacement for free, but instead they tried to charge me full price. Highly unprofessional and inappropriate

Even a basic cappuccino has that deep, rich aroma and smooth taste — really good coffee. Some cool art and chandeliers catch your eye — definitely worth a quick stop. A perfect place to snap some city photos!
What a quaint "little " bakery/bistro right in downtown Charlotte! Specialty coffee and the Cinnamon roll was amazing and the lunch items smelled delicious as well!

From out of town, visiting for a festival. This café was recommended by several locals for breakfast. Nice atmosphere and delicious pastries. The lemon raspberry was yummy. Unfortunately there was a mix up picking up my order from the dine in window, and while every employee aware was working to resolve the mix up, an employee named Zach was extremely rude and condescending about me and my responsibility to get my order in ear shot of me and many other customers waiting beside me. Because another employee was so helpful, I did not say anything about his rudenss and thanked her. I understand things happened and would very rarely directly call out an employee but this level of rudeness is worthy of it and I can only assume Zach is an owner or related to an owner for this behavior to be tolerated. I would return, but I would request Zach not be involved in my service.
Amazing 👏
Fantastic!
My favorite iced coffee in Charlotte so far. The cream cheese pastry was great as well.
Fun experience!
Food and service were terrible. Don't be distracted by the crazy decor. Atmosphere and decor were both way too loud

Amélie’s French Bakery & Café in Uptown Charlotte is a whimsical retreat that delights both the palate and the senses. The café’s eclectic décor features mismatched chandeliers, including one crafted entirely from silverware, adding to its quirky charm. Guests can indulge in signature pastries like the famed Salted Caramel Brownie, alongside a variety of French-inspired treats and beverages. Whether you’re seeking a cozy spot for coffee or a unique backdrop for conversation, Amélie’s offers a memorable experience in the heart of the city.

reviews_data.review_text: Fun place, good food, helpful staff
Cute French Cafe in Charlotte

I walked in with high expectations, drawn by the French name of the pastry shop, hoping for delicate desserts with the balanced flavors typical of French patisserie. Unfortunately, the reality was quite different. The pastries were overwhelmingly sweet and heavy, more reminiscent of American-style desserts than anything French. Disappointing overall.
Very long line, but only because food and ambiance was totally worth it!

I stopped by to grab some pastries and decided to stay and have a bite for lunch. I was assisted by two different employees, one who was very sweet and helpful, one who was dismissive, rushed (they weren’t very busy), and kind of rude.
I ordered a “tartine” with fig jam, Brie, and bacon. The baguette was sub par and borderline stale, the Brie was obviously a crème style product, and the bacon was low quality. Every time I tried to take a bite, the full slices of bacon would pull off the entire piece of bread. Just a poorly constructed afterthought.
The “salad” consisted of two GIANT pieces of kale, a few smaller torn pieces, and toppings that I ended up basically eating by themselves. I mean, completely inedible as salad. I could have gotten up and asked for a knife, but I already felt as though I was fighting for my life just trying to consume this meal peacefully, so I gave up. I actually don’t think I would go back.
The three stars are for the pastries which were decent, the one nice employee, and the ambiance.

Super cool little bistro with a hip vibe. A couple was here dressed to the nines and taking pictures in the awesome decor (though it would have been nice if they weren't in the way of people actually buying and eating things). Great food, the desserts on point, and the tartlets do travel well crosscountry!

reviews_data.review_text: A nice pastry shop and cafe with sidewalk seating to enjoy your beverage and relax watching the world like a true Parisian café and pâtisserie
Great selection of bakery. Veggie quiche a tad oily otherwise tasty. Love the decor and motif.

The only French about this place was the music in the restroom. The rest is American -  greasy food, pastries are super sweat, depressing atmosphere inside. Tried to find good coffee place in Charlotte based on reviews and this one was a mistake
amazing coffee and pastries. the cafe is almost a tourist attraction in its self ! It’s an extremely unique place !

Really disappointed. Have come here for a year and order the same thing every. Sadly, something has changed with the torts. Parts of the shell are soggy. The strawberries are water logged and also soggy. This was within a few minutes of ordering. You can see the ring in the box from the wet ring under the tort.
Great breakfast location in downtown Charlotte. A lot of seating inside and out. Great service and great food. Is within walking distance of a lot of hotels in the area. Great experience.

reviews_data.review_text: The macarons were great when I went, and the building is so pretty inside. I recommend it to anyone that I know is visiting Charlotte :)
Very nice staff. Delicious pastries.  Ambiance was calming. Strawberry danish and raspberry lemon tart was amazing.

The BEST macarons I have ever had! I stumbled upon this place while I was visiting for the ACC games and I was instantly hooked! Once I found out they shipped macarons, I ordered a dozen to ship. While there was an issue with my order, the manager I spoke to was absolutely phenomenal in getting things back in line and they were there the next day on my door step. If you want a delicious treat..try this place!
Wonderful little bakery in uptown Charlotte! Visit them, you won't be disappointed! I had their twice baked almond croissant- super yummy!

I recently visited on Sunday a French bakery nestled in the vibrant heart of downtown, and it was a delightful experience from start to finish. The ambience immediately stood out—unique and fancy, with an elegant charm that made it feel like a little slice of France amid the urban bustle. The decor was sophisticated yet welcoming, striking a perfect balance that elevated the entire visit.

The location couldn’t be better; being right in the center of downtown made it a convenient stop amidst a busy day, yet it felt like a serene escape from the surrounding hustle. What truly impressed me, though, was the wide range of options to choose from. Whether you’re craving a flaky croissant, a rich éclair, or a perfectly crafted macaron, this bakery has something for every palate. The variety was almost overwhelming—in the best way possible—showcasing authentic French flavors with a modern twist.
Very eclectic bakery and eatery. Very well furnished and dressed. The treats were delicious. Baguette and macarons.

We were hoping to dine at Amelie’s French Bakery & Cafe in uptown today and once again, they were out of quiche. You would think they would know the demand they have from their customers so they would make enough to last through the brunch hour on the weekends. However, they don’t because this happens all the time. In addition, they were out of chicken salad and also turkey so no Monte Cristo. I asked her what did they have and she basically said not a lot except for the bakery items. She said she wish she had a digital menu board so they could wipe out the items that they didn’t have so people would know. That’s not a bad idea however, how about trying to be in stock so you can serve your clientele. It’s a great place to eat when they have the food. Bummer that we had to leave. Maybe next time.

Waited close to an hour to get an unbaked pre-bake baguette like the plastic wrapped ones you buy at a grocery store and a Napoleon with completely frozen cream. Also sold out of croissants, but I think we lucked out not buying more things.
Amazing food. Friendly staff and great atmosphere.
the cashier was very overwhelming and got our orders completely messed up. i much prefer the other locations.

Amélie's is a short walk from the Kimpton hotel.  It sounded tasty, so I randomly decided to check it out one Saturday afternoon. There were plenty of patrons inside but there was no wait. And still plenty of pastries and treats to choose from.

I tried an oat chai latte, and it was delicious. So good in fact that I walked back over the next morning before we had to hit the road. I also got an almond torte, and it was really sweet. More like a dessert than a breakfast pastry.

The cafe itself had the coolest decor. There were several unique chandeliers made of things like pots and pans and kitchen utensils. There's also a lot of fun artwork. The place is huge too, with what appeared to be multiple levels of seating and plenty of tables.

I'd definitely stop by if I'm in town again. They have a whole menu I need to check out.

The food and vibe of this place are great. However, the service was disappointing. The guy with the ponytail at the checkout counter was passive-aggressive for some reason and wasn’t friendly at all. At the end of checkout, it prompts you to join the loyalty program, and I was eager to sign up. However, as I started entering my details, he canceled the screen. Additionally, when I asked him to make my order 'for here,' he ignored my request and made it 'to-go' instead. These small issues really spoiled the mood, and it made it hard to fully enjoy the vibe of the place.

I had the absolute pleasure of enjoying a delicious pastry at Amelie’s, and it was nothing short of delightful. The pastry was perfectly baked—flaky, rich, and bursting with flavor in every bite. You can really taste the love and care that goes into their creations.

Beyond the food, the atmosphere at Amelie’s is fun, vibrant, and full of charm. The eclectic decor and open, welcoming vibe make it the kind of place where you want to linger. Whether you’re catching up with a friend or just enjoying some solo time, it’s a space that instantly lifts your mood.

This is a long one…
First obvious context. When I review I consider 3 elements of my experience: atmosphere, service and food. Less obvious, I have worked across the street from Amelie’s for more than 10 yrs, and I LOVE French foods, and honestly, I’m not that hard to please. You’ll have to trust me on this because after reading this review you will doubt me.

Sadly, Amelie’s consistently disappoints me. My biggest gripe is with their ordering, food collection process - it’s confusing and customers end up asking each other questions (“where are the napkins?” You’ll find them across the wide open space far from the cutlery) because the staff seems oblivious to the general confusion and doesn’t set or manage expectations. A few years ago they did a process and space  remodel, but alas, it’s still confusing.

Nonetheless, the food used to lure me in despite this frustration with process and staff’s oblivion. But even that has become ‘meh’- not the pasties mind you they are amazing—  Sometimes heated halfway through, sometimes flavors fall short.

Fortunately for me and my French-food-obsession there are multiple French restaurants in and around CLT.  One that excels where Amelie’s flops, is Chez Marie Patisserie in South Park. They also have amazing pastries, and win on service, attitude and food as well. Plus it’s a darling little space to sit and enjoy life. I don’t work there, I don’t know anyone who works there, I’m just a fan of their sunny spot.
